                                        <div class=3D"faq-item-bottom">
                                            <p>Marginally, but not dramatic=
ally. Both are plaintext files on disk. The real advantage of .env is separ=
ation: you can back up openclaw.json (which contains your configuration log=
ic) without including the actual secret values. The SecretRef system is the=
 proper solution for secrets that need to be genuinely protected, because t=
he values never touch the config files at all.</p>

