-collapse collapse " style=3D"" data-parent=3D"#accordion-1890-1">
                                        <div class=3D"faq-item-bottom">
                                            <p>WhatsApp sessions are stored=
 as session files in <code>~/.openclaw/channels/whatsapp/</code> rather tha=
n as traditional API keys. "Rotation" for WhatsApp means re-authenticating =
via QR code when the session expires. There's no automated rotation path. K=
eep the session files in your regular backup routine and be prepared to re-=
authenticate manually every few weeks or after any session invalidation eve=
nt (phone reinstall, WhatsApp account changes, etc.).</p>

                                        </div>
