 </div>
                                    <div id=3D"faq-1890-1-4" class=3D"panel=
-collapse collapse " style=3D"" data-parent=3D"#accordion-1890-1">
                                        <div class=3D"faq-item-bottom">
                                            <p>In theory, yes, if the agent=
's tools include read access to <code>~/.openclaw/</code> and the agent can=
 be prompted to read and report files. The mitigations: use SecretRef so ac=
tual key values aren't in any file the agent can read, restrict read tool a=
ccess with a path allowlist that excludes the config directory, and treat p=
rompt injection as a real threat for any agent connected to public channels=
. The exec provider is worth thinking about from this angle too: an agent w=
ith exec tool access and a sufficiently creative attacker could potentially=
 call the secrets provider CLI directly if it's on PATH. Sandbox mode remov=
es exec access in untrusted contexts.</p>

                                        </div>
